    <name>
      <text>Solving the system of linear equations using the method of Gaussian Elimination Test</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Solve the following system of linear equations using the method of Gaussian Elimination:</p>
<p>\(
\begin{align*}
{@A8[1,1]*x@} + {@A8[1,2]*y@}+ {@A8[1,3]*z@} &= {@A8[1,4]@}\\
{@A8[2,1]*x@} + {@A8[2,2]*y@}+ {@A8[2,3]*z@} &= {@A8[2,4]@}\\
{@A8[3,1]*x@} + {@A8[3,2]*y@}+ {@A8[3,3]*z@} &= {@A8[3,4]@}
\end{align*}
\)</p>
<p>
<ol>
<li>Write the augmented matrix for the system of equations</li>
<p> [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<br>
<li>Write the RRE form of the matrix. </li>
<p>[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>
<br>
<li>Determine if the system of equations has:</li>
</p>[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p>
<ol>
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>\(
\begin{align*}
{@A8[1,1]*x@} + {@A8[1,2]*y@}+ {@A8[1,3]*z@} &= {@A8[1,4]@}\\
{@A8[2,1]*x@} + {@A8[2,2]*y@}+ {@A8[2,3]*z@} &= {@A8[2,4]@}\\
{@A8[3,1]*x@} + {@A8[3,2]*y@}+ {@A8[3,3]*z@} &= {@A8[3,4]@}
\end{align*}
\)</p>

<p>The Augmented matrix will be:  {@A8@}</p>
<p> We'll take the matrix from the previous step beginning with the augmented matrix above and perform the following operations.</p>
<p>\(
\begin{align*}
\textbf{Step 1}  && R_1 \leftarrow {@1/mult_const[3]@}\times R_1 : {@A9@} \\
\textbf{Step 2}  &&  R_2 \leftarrow R_2{@-add_const[6]@}R_1 : {@A10@}\\

\textbf{Step 3} & & R_3 \leftarrow R_3{@-add_const[5]@}R_1 : {@A11@}\\

\textbf{Step 4} & & R_2 \leftarrow {@1/mult_const[2]@}R_2 : {@A12@} \\

\textbf{Step 5} & & R_1 \leftarrow R_1{@-add_const[4]@}R_2 : {@A13@}\\

\textbf{Step 6} & & R_3 \leftarrow R_3{@-add_const[3]@}R_2 : {@A14@}\\

\textbf{Step 7} & & R_3 \leftarrow {@1/mult_const[1]@}R_3 : {@A15@} \\

\textbf{Step 8} & & R_1 \leftarrow R_1{@-add_const[2]@}R_3 : {@A16@}\\

\textbf{Step 9} & & R_2 \leftarrow R_2{@-add_const[1]@}R_3 : {@A17@} 
\end{align*}
\)</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Therefore, the solutions of the system will be \( x= {@ans_x@}, y={@ans_y@}, z={@ans_z@} \)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
